The peregrine falcon holds the title for the fastest animal in the world when it comes to diving speeds. It can reach up to 240 miles per hour (386 kilometers per hour) during its hunting dive, also known as stooping.

However, if we consider the top speed of terrestrial animals, the cheetah is often cited as the fastest on land. Cheetahs are capable of reaching speeds up to about 70 miles per hour (112 kilometers per hour).
